# Leet Alert — docs + visual stay in sync with the app

Whenever **any chat or agent** changes **`apps/alert-theleetclub-com`** in ways that affect **routes, screens, layout, permissions behavior, operator-visible copy, or data/API behavior**, finish the same task by updating **all** of:

1. **`apps/alert-theleetclub-com/PRODUCT-PROTOTYPE.md`** — routes table, audience/permissions, changelog row (newest first).
2. **`apps/alert-theleetclub-com/docs/product-prototype/visual-prototype.svg`** — schematic wireframes must match navigation and primary widgets (add panels if new screens matter for PM review).
3. **`npm run doc:pdf`** from **`apps/alert-theleetclub-com`** (WSL if needed) → refresh **`PRODUCT-PROTOTYPE.pdf`** and commit it with the markdown/SVG.

**UI rule:** Do **not** add “prototype”, “draft”, or experimental badges/wording **inside the running app**. Roadmap and fidelity belong in **`PRODUCT-PROTOTYPE.md`** / PDF / SVG only.

Full checklist and deploy lives in **`leet-alert-prototype-doc.mdc`** and **`deploy-gas-and-people-api.mdc`**.
